<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="164" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="37.[805,1399,587,1929]" pageId="37" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[807,1035,1510,1530]" pageId="37" pageNumber="164">HABITAT &amp; ECOLOGY.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1282,1508,1530]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="37" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thunbergiiflora">
<emphasis box="[1046,1282,1508,1530]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="164">Barleria thunbergiiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in open grassland rich in geoxylic suffrutices on deep Kalahari Sands on plateaux above rivers, and in seasonal marshes (“tengas”) at 1190 – 1400 m alt. It appears to occur on more nutrient-poor sites than most of the allied species in sect. 
<emphasis box="[1178,1257,1661,1682]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="164">Somalia</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
